        <def>(BUDDH:) Ancient state north of India; it is doubtful which place this name refers to and different sources give different kinds of information (some think this is a corruption of Jiābìshìguó 迦畢試國 (skr. Kapiśa), or a reference to Jiébǐshě 劫比舍 (skr. Karpiśaya); Rémuset thinks it might refer to today's Kabul (Kophes); Lévi and Chavannes think it refers to Kaśmīra (which is maybe the most likely explanation)</def>
